snippet.textDisplay: I've got a few things to say: first of all, you are BEAUTIFUL no matter what. Secondly, I understand what you said about the social aspect of it, and that's a really difficult commitment. I've been a vegetarian since birth so I am very used to it and also it's far easier than veganism, and I understand especially if you're switching from a meat-eating diet, there are a lot of changes in your life. However, at least from this video you seem to be doing a lot better not just for things like skin and hair, but also emotionally, so what I recommend, if you don't want to become fully vegan/vegetarian, is have 1 week a month where you are vegan (and this can increase gradually if you get more comfortable with it). I think this way you can continue eating meat but also feel close to how you've felt with this challenge. I do have friends who do this and it works really well for them! It's your choice in the end though, but remember, no matter what, you are beautiful inside and out.
